			<h3 class="first">
								<a href="#p56665">Pinging - How to prevent it</a>
			</h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=56665&amp;sid=e04bf280d2e70ab04ccfebe346a6a204#p56665"><img src="./styles/Carbon/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>			by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27070&amp;sid=e04bf280d2e70ab04ccfebe346a6a204">iistapp</a></strong> on Sun Apr 24, 2011 10:37 pm			<br />([msg=56665]see Pinging - How to prevent it[/msg])
			</p>

			
			<div class="content">Hey people of HTS!<br /><br />I play this game, and I have a feeling someone is pinging me, because now and then I get some serious amount of lag in-game, is this possible to do against a simple computer like you have at home?<br /><br />If so, how would I prevent it? Is there a way to log the pings and their IP so I can report it to my ISP or something?</div>

			
		</div>

