								<a href="#p56698">Re: Pinging - How to prevent it</a>
			</h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=56698&amp;sid=e04bf280d2e70ab04ccfebe346a6a204#p56698"><img src="./styles/Carbon/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>			by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=29819&amp;sid=e04bf280d2e70ab04ccfebe346a6a204">sanddbox</a></strong> on Tue Apr 26, 2011 9:44 pm			<br />([msg=56698]see Re: Pinging - How to prevent it[/msg])
			</p>

			
			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>iistapp wrote:</cite>Well it must be something, because It's not my bandwith or anything that can cause it, and it happens only when of course, some guys from the &quot;opposite team&quot; comes and kill me, I end up being &quot;stuck&quot; because of some heavy lag sort of thing, and I can't heal or barely move so I'm dead in no time.<br /><br />So what else do you believe it to be?</div></blockquote><br /><br />Most likely it's just server lag. Regardless, as Goatboy said, a simple ping attack will do nothing to cause you to lag. A DoS would, but is very unlikely seeing as how it sounds like it happens multiple different times with different players.<br /><br />TL;DR: 99% chance it's the game server (or your computer) lagging).</div>

